## âš™ï¸ Characteristics of C

C has often been termed a **â€œpseudo high-level languageâ€** or a **â€œmiddle-level languageâ€** by many programmers.  
This is not due to any lack of power but rather because of its **ability to access low-level system functions** while still supporting **high-level programming constructs**.

- C was **specifically invented to implement UNIX**.  
- C instructions are **compiled into assembly code**, meaning:
  - Depending on the **complexity** of the program.
  - And the **compilerâ€™s optimization capabilities**,  
  **C code can run almost as fast as assembly.**

