## ğŸ§© Background and Evolution

- **Ken Thompson** created the **B language** in **1969**, derived from **Martin Richardâ€™s BCPL (Basic Combined Programming Language)**.  
- Using **assembly language** and **B**, he developed the **initial versions of the UNIX operating system**.  
- Later, **Dennis Ritchie** evolved B into **C**, providing greater power and efficiency, which eventually became the foundation of modern programming.

